<%= render PageTitle::View.new(text: "Bulk upload placement data for trainee records") %>

<%= content_for(:breadcrumbs) do %>
  <%= render GovukComponent::BackLinkComponent.new(
    text: "How to use this service",
    href: guidance_path,
    ) %>
<% end %>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds-from-desktop">
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Bulk upload placement data for trainee records</h1>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">You can use Register trainee teachers (Register) to bulk upload placement data for trainee records.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Add placement data</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">You can bulk add placement data to registered trainee records.</p>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">You can change placement details  <%= govuk_link_to("manually in an individual trainee’s record", manually_registering_trainees_guidance_path) %>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How to bulk upload placement data</h2>

    <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
      <li>Make sure you are signed into Register. Click into ‘Bulk updates’ in the main navigation.</li>
      <li>Download a CSV file listing the trainees with missing placement data.</li>
      <li>Add missing placement URNs.</li>
      <li>Upload the CSV file.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">1. Sign into Register</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">Once you have signed into Register, you can <%= govuk_link_to("access the bulk update feature", new_bulk_update_placements_path) %>.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">2. Download a CSV file listing trainees with missing placement data</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">For the purposes of the performance profile sign off deadline in February each academic year, the CSV file will only include data for all trainees who:</p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>gained QTS or EYTS in the most recent academic year</li>
      <li>do not have the minimum placements recorded for the ITT route</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">The CSV will not include:</p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>trainees who have deferred or withdrawn</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">3. Add missing placement details to the CSV file</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">
      Enter the placement URNs in the placement columns. You can record up to 5 placements in the CSV file.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">
      If the trainee had more than 5 placements, add those extra placements to the trainee record manually.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">You can find the URNs using <a href="https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/Search" class="govuk-link" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">Get information about schools</a>.</p>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">You cannot add information in bulk if the school or setting does not have a URN. Add those placements to the trainee record manually.</p>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">If you do not currently hold the information for a placement, leave the cell empty. Overwriting the content of a cell with a new URN will replace the existing placement with your new URN if it is a valid URN.</p>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">If you want to delete a placement, you will need to sign in to Register and do this manually in the trainee record.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">4. Upload the CSV file</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body-m">Ensure you have saved the file as a CSV file. It will not be accepted in any other format.</p>
  </div>
</div>
